<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1216,1668]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,338,1410,1436]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">Chorotype.</emphasis>
Central Mediterranean: its known distribution includes 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1110,1410,1436]" name="Algeria" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and Sardinia only (
<bibRefCitation author="Liberti, G." pageId="32" pageNumber="371" pagination="153 - 194" refId="ref36231" refString="Liberti, G. (1995 a) Revisione delle specie italiane del genere Aplocnemus Stephens (Coleoptera Melyridae Rhadalinae). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 73, 153 - 194." type="journal article" year="1995">Liberti 1995a</bibRefCitation>
). Affinities: rather close to 
<emphasis box="[556,574,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rottenberg, 1870" authorityName="Rottenberg" authorityYear="1870" box="[590,995,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Aplocnemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus" subGenus="Aplocnemus">
(
<emphasis box="[600,618,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[644,778,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">marginatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rottenberg, A. von" box="[786,995,1449,1475]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" pagination="235 - 260" refId="ref38908" refString="Rottenberg, A. von (1870) Beitrage zur Coleopteren Fauna von Sicilien (Zweistes Stuck). Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 14, 235 - 260." type="journal article" year="1870">Rottenberg, 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in Sicily and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,234,1488,1514]" name="Greece" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Liberti, G. &amp; Zinetti, F." box="[249,561,1488,1514]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" pagination="45 - 53" refId="ref36682" refString="Liberti, G. &amp; Zinetti, F. (2009) Nota su alcuni Aplocnemus italiani nuovi o poco noti, con descrizione di Aplocnemus etruscus n. sp. (Coleoptera Dasytidae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 141 (1), 45 - 53." type="journal article" year="2009">Liberti &amp; Zinetti 2009: 49</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1216,1668]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,1526,1552]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">Notes.</emphasis>
A species easily recognizable by the shape of pronotum, rather depressed with well visible anterior angles, and by the reddish margin all around the body, more evident on sides of pronotum. Already reported for 
<collectingRegion box="[193,291,1604,1630]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="32" pageNumber="371">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bertolini, S." box="[338,520,1604,1630]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" pagination="19 - 24" refId="ref34147" refString="Bertolini, S. (1899 - 1904) Catalogo dei Coleotteri d'Italia. Rivista Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 19 - 24 (Appendices), 144 pp." type="book chapter" year="1899">Bertolini (1899</bibRefCitation>
–1904: 73), 
<bibRefCitation author="Luigioni, P." box="[665,914,1604,1630]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" pagination="1 - 1160" refId="ref36900" refString="Luigioni, P. (1929) Coleotteri d'Italia. Catalogo sinonimico-topografico-bibliografico. Memorie della Pontificia Accademia delle Scienze Nuovi Lincei, 13, 1 - 1160." type="journal article" year="1929">Luigioni (1929: 626)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Porta, A." box="[973,1126,1604,1630]" pageId="32" pageNumber="371" refId="ref38316" refString="Porta, A. (1929) Fauna Coleopterorum Italica. III - Diversicornia. Stabilimento Tipografico Piacentino, Piacenza, 466 pp." type="book" year="1929">Porta (1929)</bibRefCitation>
. Despite being rare, it has been repeatedly collected with traps at Marganai (see below) all year round except in summer.
</paragraph>
